review_blob: Good drinking beer.  Fluffy head dissipated quickly.  good carbonation. decent malt character with a crisp bite. Good flavor for style. Nice w/crabs
reddish brown with a nice white cap, that slowy dissapates.  Not overly sour, just enough. Cleans pallette nicely.  nothing fancy, good refreshing flemish ale.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Bottle a little undercarbed.  Thin head that dissipated quickly.  Good aroma of mollasses.  Tastes of raisins, sugar and mollases, slight alcohol residual warming.  overall an interesting beer to drink that is well balanced.
Red copper pour with very little head. Dissipates quickly. Aroma of honey and spices. Lot of residual sweetness with a powerful honey aftertaste.  good concept that got out of control.
poured a dark brown with a fluffy white head with good retention. mouthfeel a little light for style.  Grainy flavor that finishes dry.  Good drink but nothing I would go running for.
Dark brown, with nice thick two finger head with great retention.  aroma was stale and flavor was bland. Bottled could have oxidized due to cardboard taste.  No pop or excitement out of this one.
beer_name: Hook and Ladder Backdraft Brown Ale

beer_brewer_name: Old Dominion Brewing Company (Coastal Brewing Co.)
review_blob: Typical stout color, pours to a small reddish copper head that dissipates very quickly. light mouthfeel for style. lightly oaked, dont get much of the vanilla. Good, but better available

Well crafted barleywine aged on oak 2007 edition. Clear dark copper color with fluffy head. Head was thick and maintained for quite some time. Unusual for a high ABV beer.  Good malt hop balance with fruity to start with strong dry bittering hops to finish. Any residual sweetness is masked by the light oak tannins and hop balance. Too drinkable. Goes down quick so watch out...
beer_name: Schlafly Reserve Barleywine Style Ale Aged On Oak

review_blob: one of the best pours, with a big white lacy head, that delivers great fruit esters. High carbonation makes this beer tickle the tongue and delivers a slight residual sweetness at the end. For 8.5%ABV this will sneak up on you. Very little alcohol flavor, very slight warming at end.
Good smokebeer. Less smokey than the higher alcohol Urbock makes this more enjoyable.  Makes you crave bacon, or a salty piece of meat. Something to enjoy during a nice beer dinner

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: great  beer. Good aroma of fruit, head dissipated quickly. great mouthfeel and flavor with tastes of cherry and spices balancing nicely. all around excellent beer.
Great pumpkin brew.  Good deep golden orange hue w/ good spice balance.  Easy drinking beer. Clear and smooth..
deep golden orange color with nice fluffy head.  Malty w/ no hop aroma.  Some residual sweetness.  Easy to drink, clean and soft...

Wow, I feel like Im drinking in a meat smoker. Incredible smoke aroma is almost overpowering.  The beer is smooth, clear witha dark amber hue.  Head was big and fluffy but reduced quickly.  For my first rauchbier this beer makes you think during every sip.  Good example of the style.

Great all around beer.  smooth smoky aroma that maintains throughout the bottle. Thick tan head holds well for a little while.  Malty, melanoidin flavor that would go great with something salty. Alcohol heat not present, a little warming in the stomache.  Fun beer to drink...

Good beer with nice thick lacy white head, decent retention. Clear golden yellow color with consistent carbonation. flavors of clove banana with a punch of alcohol at the finish.  Refreshing drink for a high gravity beer
Good bready aroma with rocky white head. Good retention. golden amber appearance with solid melanoidn presence. Slight yeast taste, but to style. Good all around beer.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Best choice when only faced with larger commercial fizzy brews.  Limited head, good carbonation. While not too familiar with MHs other beer, I would expect this beer would be pretty good without the apricot essence.  Good maltiness underneath the fruitness
Golden with great fluffy head. Great hop citrusy hop aroma coupled with good malty balance. Thin mouthfeel, well carbed.  packed with hops...Good IPA

Golden clear pour with with nice thin frothy head. Very carbonated, Citrus hop notes, clean, well attenuated with little residual sweetness. slight yeast bite and alchohol warmth in finish... good beer

The Hibiscus really give a different look to a normal wheat beer.  Pinkish amber with a nice fluffy white head.  Aroma is laced with a lingering floral aroma.  The beer was smooth and delicate.  Nothing stood out, maybe a little taste of brett? Probably would be  good beer to bathe in if you wanted to smell like a flowery beer.
Pours a nice copper color with a huge fluffy brown head. Big hop flavor gives way to a nice residual sweetness.  Smell and flavor of a citrus hop dominates the flavor. Enjoyable beer...

Yellow orange hue with quickly disapating head. Mouthfeel is light with very little aftertaste.  Taste like a bland orange. Acidic at first, but becomes completely bland.  Too much orange peel, needs some additional ingredients to add mouthfeel and head retention...
Cloudy Orange hue, full of yeast sediment and alcohol.  Sweet, fruity flavor that is very abrupt on the tongue.  Good warmth from alcohol makes this a nice sipper...
Pours to a nice tan frothy head.  Large amount of yeast sediment entered glass which resulted in some yeast bite.  Head slowy faded away.  Sharp flavor that settles softens as you taste.
Thick white head that disepated quickly. Golden orange in color with good sweetness. Dry to finish. Nicely carbonated,
